    <h2>📅 10/03/25</h2>

    <!-- Vulnerabilities Section -->
    <div class="news-item">
        <h2>🔥 Vulnerabilities</h2>

        <p>📡 <b>ESP32 Bluetooth Chip Has Undocumented Commands Allowing Device Spoofing</b><br>
        Hidden vendor-specific commands in **ESP32 microcontrollers** allow **RAM modification, MAC spoofing, and data access**, raising supply chain concerns.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/undocumented-commands-found-in-bluetooth-chip-used-by-a-billion-devices/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>⚠️ <b>Three VMware Zero-Day Vulnerabilities Put Cloud Providers at Risk</b><br>
        Flaws in **ESXi, Workstation, and Fusion** enable **VM escapes**, leading to **widespread breaches** if left unpatched.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.darkreading.com/remote-workforce/zero-days-risk-vm-escape-attacks/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    </div>

    <!-- Adversaries Section -->
    <div class="news-item">
        <h2>🕵️ Adversaries & Attacks</h2>

        <p>🚗 <b>Fake Parking Violation Scam Spreading in US Cities</b><br>
        Residents receive **phishing texts** about **fake unpaid parking tickets**, leading to **identity theft & financial fraud**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/us-cities-warn-of-wave-of-unpaid-parking-phishing-texts/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>🎥 <b>Netflix Phishing Scam Uses AI to Steal Credentials</b><br>
        Fake emails claim **"account hold" issues**, tricking users into **entering login & payment details** on a phishing page.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.cysecurity.news/2025/03/netflix-users-warned-about-ai-powered.html/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>🔔 <b>Push Notifications Used for Gift Card & Sweepstakes Scams</b><br>
        Attackers trick users into **allowing notifications**, leading to **endless ad fraud and financial theft**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://hackread.com/what-happens-when-push-notifications-go-malicious/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>📡 <b>Microsoft Dismantles Storm-0408 Malvertising Campaign</b><br>
        Malicious ads on **GitHub, Discord, & Dropbox** infected **nearly 1M Windows devices** with **banking trojans & ransomware**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://hackread.com/microsoft-dismantle-malvertising-github-discord-dropbox/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>🛑 <b>Akira Ransomware Uses Unsecured Webcam to Bypass EDR</b><br>
        Attackers **used a Linux-based webcam with remote access** as a pivot point to **encrypt an entire network**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/175103/cyber-crime/akira-ransomware-gang-used-unsecured-webcam-bypass-edr.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>🦠 <b>Desert Dexter Malware Targets MENA Region via Fake News Links</b><br>
        Affected victims in **Libya, Saudi Arabia, Turkey, and Egypt** had **crypto wallets & data stolen** through phishing.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.cysecurity.news/2025/03/malware-alert-as-desert-dexter-strikes.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>🔧 <b>Mirai Botnet Exploiting Zero-Day in Edimax IP Cameras</b><br>
        Attackers **remotely control unpatched cameras**, using them for **DDoS & credential theft**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/175060/hacking/mirai-based-botnets-exploit-cve-2025-1316-zero-day-in-edimax-ip-cameras.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    </div>

